                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.199/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 15, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>B–378. Your 393 of November 13, 1 p.m. and 394 of November 14, noon.<note n="97"
                        xml:id="d368fn97">Neither printed.</note> There has been little press
                    comment here regarding reports you mention that Chapman will return to Bilbao as
                    an “agent” or in a diplomatic or other representative capacity with the
                    insurgent authorities. In reply to press inquiries we have made it clear that
                    Chapman will return to his post in his capacity as consul only; that as in the
                    case of our consulate at Malaga the consul at Bilbao will resume his duties
                    because we feel conditions now make it safe to do so; and that the maintenance
                    of our consulates in insurgent territory involves no question of
                    recognition.</p>
                <p>In view of Bay’s report that General Franco has authorized the return of Chapman
                    to Bilbao and has undertaken to telegraph at once to facilitate his entry at
                    Irun, Chapman should make every effort to conclude arrangements for immediate
                    return.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
